Enrico Lopez-Yañez is currently the Principal Pops Conductor of the Nashville Symphony after serving as the assistant conductor since 2017.
Lopez-Yañez has led performances with artists such as Nas, Toby Keith, Trisha Yearwood, The Beach Boys, Kenny Loggins, Renée Elise Goldsberry, and the Marcus Roberts Trio.

In the summer of 2016, Lopez-Yañez served as Assistant Conductor to Christoph Eschenbach and Valery Gergiev for the National Youth Orchestra of the United States's Carnegie Hall, New York state, and European tour performances.
